==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feat
<hw>Feat</hw> <pr>(f⟦emac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fet</ets>, OF. <ets>fet</ets>, <ets>fait</ets>, F. <ets>fait</ets>,
<ets>factum</ets>, fr. L. <ets>facere</ets>, <ets>factum</ets>, to make
or do. Cf. <er>Fact</er>, <er>Feasible</er>, <er>Do</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An act; a deed; an exploit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The warlike <qex>feats</qex> I have done.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A striking act of strength, skill, or cunning; a
trick; <as>as, <ex>feats</ex> of horsemanship, or of
dexterity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Feat
<hw>Feat</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To form; to fashion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the more mature,⟦br⟧
A glass that <qex>feated</qex> them.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Feat
<hw>Feat</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Feater</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Featest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[F. <ets>fait</ets> made, shaped,
fit, p. p. of <ets>faire</ets> to make or do. See <er>Feat</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Dexterous in movements or service; skillful;
neat; nice; pretty.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Never master had a page . . . so <qex>feat</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And look how well my garments sit upon me --⟦br⟧
Much <qex>feater</qex> than before.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feat-bodied</ent>⟦br⟧
